              <h2> 1-Therapeutic Play.</h2>
                             <p> Therapeutic Play is the use of play as a means to achieve therapeutic or educational goals, primarily employed in the field of psychological therapy to support psychological and social development, especially in children. The aim of therapeutic play is to promote positive interaction and improve social, emotional, and motor skills.


        <p>





</p>
            <h2>2- Art and Creativity.</h2>
            <p>"Expressing art and creativity. This can include visual arts such as drawing and sculpting, as well as creative activities involving creative thinking and innovation in various fields. Arts and creativity are considered a means of expressing individual ideas and emotions, promoting innovative and experimental thinking."





</p>
        </p>
        <p>
            <h2>3- Group Therapy.</h2>
            <p>The abbreviation for the described term "refers to a form of psychotherapy in which a small group of individuals, typically led by a trained therapist, come together to discuss and explore their issues, share experiences, and provide support to one another. Group therapy offers a supportive and collaborative environment where participants can gain insights, receive feedback, and learn coping strategies from both the therapist and fellow group members. This approach is widely used in mental health treatment for various concerns, allowing individuals to connect with others who may be facing similar challenges" is GT.</p>
        </p>
        <p>
            <h2>4- Mindfulness Practices.</h2>
            <p> "Mindfulness Practices" are activities promoting full present-moment awareness, such as meditation and deep breathing, fostering non-judgmental attention to thoughts and surroundings for stress reduction and improved well-being.




</p>
        </p>
        <p>
            <h2>5- Educational Workshops.</h2>
            <p>"Educational Workshops" are interactive sessions that provide participants with knowledge and skills on specific educational topics, fostering practical insights and enhancing competencies.




</p>
        </p>
        <p>
            <h2>6- Physical Exercise.</h2>
            <p>"Physical Exercise" involves bodily activities to improve fitness and overall health, encompassing various forms such as aerobic exercises, strength training, and flexibility exercises. Regular exercise is linked to enhanced well-being and a reduced risk of chronic diseases.

</p>
        </p>
        <p>
            <h2>7- Music and Movement Therapy.</h2>
            <p> "Music and Movement Therapy" utilizes music and movement to enhance emotional, physical, and cognitive well-being. It involves structured activities to address therapeutic goals, benefiting various populations for stress relief, emotional expression, and improved quality of life.
</p>
        </p>
        <p>
            <h2>8- Storytelling.</h2>
            <p>"Storytelling" is the art of conveying narratives through spoken or written words to entertain, educate, or convey messages, utilizing characters, plot, and themes to engage and create a meaningful experience.





 </p>
        </p>
        <p>
            <h2>9- Counseling Sessions.</h2>
            <p> "Counseling Sessions" are scheduled meetings with a counselor or therapist to discuss and address personal challenges, emotions, and concerns, aiming to enhance mental well-being through guidance, coping strategies, and positive changes.

</p>
        </p>
        <p>
            <h2>10- Parent-Child Bonding.</h2>
           <p>"Parent-Child Bonding" is the emotional connection between parents and children, established through nurturing interactions, play, and shared experiences, fostering trust, security, and supporting the child's overall development.





</p>
        </p>
        
   
